<T>__{dissolve to:}
<L>__{interior bunkhouse night}
<A>__{radio's pulling in some jazz music out of new orleans. prisoners hit their bunks as the floorwalker does the nightly head count. he stops at claude and ray's empty bunks, glancing around, puzzled.}
<L>__{exterior dillard's porch night}
<A>__{dillard smokes a cigarette on the swing. his wife steps out with a fresh bourbon and ice. suddenly, sirens start to wail and emergency floodlights blaze to life at camp 8.}
<L>__{exterior field night}
<A>__{hounds scramble down from the back of a truck and gather around the dog boy. he holds out a handful of soiled laundry and a dozen snouts sniff it thoroughly. nearby, dillard gathers a dozen men with rifles and flashlights into a posse. he puts a cigarette in his mouth. hoppin' bob lights it for him.}
